## 5. State Management Rules

| Data Type | Where it lives | Why |
|---|---|---|
| API / server data | React Query | Caching, refetch, staleness |
| Global client state | Redux Toolkit + MMKV | Auth session, user prefs |
| Local UI state | `useState` | Ephemeral, component-scoped |
| Navigation state | React Navigation | Screen-level concern |

> ⚠️ **Never put raw API data in Redux.** Redux is for client state — not a cache for server responses.

