## 6. Network Layer

Build in this order — one concern per layer:

```
1. Axios instance     → one instance per client (public / private)
2. Request interceptor  → attach token, add request ID, set adaptive timeout
3. Response interceptor → handle 401, queue token refresh, retry after refresh
4. Retry logic        → exponential backoff, retryable status codes only (5xx, network errors)
5. API functions      → thin wrappers — no business logic inside
```

### Token Contract
```
Header key: "token"   ← existing backend contract, don't break this
```

### Retry Rules
```
✅ Retry on: 500, 502, 503, 504, network timeout
❌ Never retry: 400, 401, 403, 404, 422
```

