## 11. The 4 Layers — Apply to Every Problem

When designing any feature, answer all four layers before writing code:

```
Layer 1 — What can the user DO?
          (actions, flows, edge cases)

Layer 2 — What DATA do we need?
          (shape, source, ownership)

Layer 3 — How does data MOVE and CHANGE?
          (fetch, mutate, cache, sync)

Layer 4 — What can go WRONG?
          (network failures, race conditions, stale data, auth expiry)
```

> Apply this to every PR, every feature, every system design question.

